The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited Iraq and addressed the unrest in the country. He assured Prime Minister Al Mahdi that the US supports peaceful protestors and encouraged him to listen to their calls for reform. Pence also reiterated the US commitment to an independent and sovereign Iraq and expressed concerns about the influence of Iran in the country. He mentioned that President Trump's decision to maintain troops in Syria to secure the oil fields was greatly encouraged by the Kurdish people, who fought alongside the US against ISIS. Pence stated that the US will continue to support its allies in the region and maintain a presence in Syria and Iraq. There was no confusion among the Kurdish leadership regarding President Trump's commitment to their cause, according to Pence.